      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PIN UP SHEILA (1) led from barrier rise to record a tough win on debut last start over this distance at Canterbury. Kept ticking over since that success four weeks ago with a Randwick trial on 12 June. Smart filly who will give them something to catch again. SAMBUCA SKY (3) went straight to the lead and gave nothing else a chance when fresh from a four-month spell last time out over 900m at Scone. Tougher assignment today but she is back in great shape and open to plenty of further improvement. SCURO STAR (2) picked up impressively in the closing stages to score on debut over this distance at Hawkesbury recently. Respect Peter Snowden's decision to bring her to town. Definite contender. TATIANA (9) last raced when down the track in the Group 3 Widden Stakes over today's journey at Rosehill in January. Trialling well and looks a chance first-up back in midweek company. BONVOY (5) looks the pick of the first starters after her recent trial win at this course.",
